Reasoning: The paper discusses the design and testing of a decision-theoretic advising support tool for undergraduates, which involves human-computer interaction (HCI) and user-centered design principles. Therefore, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also touches on issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CY), natural language processing (cs.CL), software engineering (cs.SE), and computer education (cs.CE) as they relate to academic advising.
